description:
In this part of the Walter Veith testimony, Walter Veith talks about his university career after he became a Christian. How did he manage to hold onto his position as professor in the sciences when he no longer believed evolution? Walter shares his challenges while working at universities in South Africa and talks about the riots on campus and how they affected him.
  
 He talks about his introduction to the writings of Ellen G. White and how he began his research on Spirit of Prophecy health and diet statements. Sonica talks about the serious problems she had with asthma and the connection between asthma and dairy. Walter discusses the opposition he experienced from the dairy industry and church members. Hear how God led them through the challenges and prepared them for greater difficulties.

For more lectures please visit:
http://amazingdiscoveries.tv/c/22/Walter_Veith/
